.SH CONFIGURATION
.SS "MCP Client Configuration"
Add to your MCP client config (e.g., .cursor/mcp.json):
.PP
.RS
.nf
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "exarp": {
      "command": "/path/to/venv/bin/python",
      "args": ["-m", "project_management_automation.server"],
      "env": {
        "PYTHONPATH": "/path/to/project-management-automation"
      }
    }
  }
}
.fi
.RE
.SS "Environment Variables"
.TP
.B EXARP_PROJECT_ROOT
Override automatic project root detection.
.TP
.B EXARP_LOG_LEVEL
Logging level (DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR).
.TP
.B EXARP_WISDOM_SOURCE
Daily wisdom source (pistis_sophia, bofh, tao, stoic, bible, etc.).
.TP
.B EXARP_WISDOM_DISABLED
Set to 1 to disable daily wisdom in scorecards.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I pyproject.toml
Project configuration and metadata.
.TP
.I PROJECT_GOALS.md
Project goals for task alignment analysis.
.TP
.I .todo2/state.todo2.json
Todo2 task state file.
.TP
.I .cursor/mcp.json
MCP server configuration for Cursor.
.TP
.I .github/workflows/ci.yml
CI/CD workflow for GitHub Actions.
.TP
.I scripts/dependency_security_config.json
Security scanner configuration.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Server started successfully or tool completed.
.TP
.B 1
Error during startup or tool execution.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start the server directly:
.RS
.B python -m project_management_automation.server
.RE
.PP
Run a tool from command line:
.RS
.B python -m project_management_automation.tools.project_scorecard
.RE
.PP
Generate HTML overview:
.RS
.B python -m project_management_automation.tools.project_overview \\
.B "    output_format=html output_path=docs/OVERVIEW.html
.RE
.PP
Run daily automation:
.RS
.B python -m project_management_automation.scripts.automate_daily
.RE
.PP
Scan for security vulnerabilities:
.RS
.B python -m project_management_automation.tools.dependency_security \\
.B "    languages='["python"]'
.RE
